Rating: 2
This was fine. Good even, but rice that takes some time, requires a recipe, and needs 2 pots and 2 heat sources should be more than just rice + fruit. If I make this again, I will add some seasonings such as cinnamon, cardamom, or even cook with chicken broth. It was VERY pretty, and looked lovely on the plate next to epicurious' "Spiced Moroccan chicken with onions and prunes" so that was good. And it did taste good, but it tasted like rice and fruit mixed together instead of a dish in and of itself that creates its own distinct flavor after the ingredients cook. P.S. Lenore: Trader Jos has shelled roasted but not salted pistachios that are inexpensive and work great in recipes.

Rating: 3
Thanks to other reviewers, I cut down on the salt and was comfortable using dried apricots since no fresh ones in my market. I took dish to a potluck dinner and baked it there, which worked fairly well. Guests were very complimentary about it but no one went back for 4 helpings, as happened at another reviewer's. Next time I'll try to find shelled pistachios since I doubled the recipe and it seemed to take forever to shell those nuts!

