Rating: 2
This is a nice way to make rice - I've never baked it before. I used brown basmati rice which meant I needed to keep adding water during the baking process so it wasn't crunchy - my own fault. As a result, the pistachios lost their crunchiness. I think next time I'll add them at the end. I also used dried apricots instead of fresh. Overall a very pleasing dish.

Rating: 4
I've made this twice and everyone loved this dish. It's simple and looks much nicer than white rice. The first time it was too salty so I halved (1 T) the salt the next time and found it was still too salty. Next time I'm going to use only 2 teaspoons salt and see how that is.

Rating: 3
